flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Nightly or on-demand planning run triggered by updated forecast, supplier capacity change, or lead-time exception.]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Consolidate demand, inventory, orders, supplier and contract data into the planning subject area]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Process Builder - Orchestrate integrated should-cost and capacity scenario runs with supplier inputs]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Data Science / Remote Functions - Rank and generate recommended integrated demand allocations and supplier shortlist]
  N3 --> N4{PB: CWB Lifecycle - Present recommendations for accept/override and capture decision}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Process Builder - Persist finalized plan and supplier shortlist to ERP and APS and trigger execution]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Notification / UI Screen - Notify suppliers and stakeholders and surface results on UI]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Aligned Plan and Source: reduced total cost of ownership, protected margins, improved on-time delivery and feasible supplier allocations across SKUs and locations; finalized plan and supplier shortlist persisted to ERP/APS and notifications sent to suppliers/stakeholders.]
  N4 -->|Scenario results satisfy cost and cap...| B1[Auto-accept recommendation and proceed with writeback to S4 and Kinaxis; notify suppliers]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Faster execution; plan and supplier shortlist finalized automatically]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Scenario shows constraint violations ...| B2[Open CWB Lifecycle for manual review and targeted resolution (negotiation, reprioritization, alternative suppliers)]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Human-in-the-loop resolves trade-offs; modified scenario re-run if needed]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Supplier capacity shortfall for criti...| B3[Process Builder triggers alternate supplier evaluation and re-runs should-cost/capacity scenarios to reallocate demand]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Alternate sourcing selected and validated, minimizing service disruption]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]